Mutharika beat out opposition leader Lazarus Chakwera with 38.57% of the vote, the Malawi Electoral Commission said on Monday, but Chakwera, a former Christian pastor, was close on his heels, with 35.41%. Deputy President Saulos Chilima of the United Transformation Movement came in third, with 20.24% of the votes. Electoral commission chairperson, Justice Jane Ansah, announced the results on Monday in Malawi's commercial capital, Blantyre. --News24--